  "doc_id": "47348",
  "text": "Colorectal cancer (CRC) is the second leading cause of cancer-related death among all malignancies worldwide [CITATION_1] . Despite surgical operation, radiotherapy, chemotherapy and personalized medicine have strongly prolonged survival of CRC patients, the 5-year relative survival remains less than 50% [CITATION_2] . In view of genomic variations, epigenomic alterations and transcriptional deregulation, CRC is often signatured with heterogeneous behaviors and a couple of molecular subtypes have been proposed, which describe detailed pictures of tumor biology mechanisms.",
